notesStmt.note: Title supplied by cataloger (Zacour-Hirsch); name is spelled Fidele in manuscript, Fedeli in reference sources.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Reports of Venetian ambassadors, the first is a report on the two states of Florence and Siena recently united under Duke Cosimo I (de' Medici), and on Cosimo himself (there is an abridged version of item 1 in UPenn Ms. Codex 577; and another version of item 3 in Ms. Codex 551).

supportDesc.extent: 242 leaves : 254 x 191 (201 x 118) mm. bound to 262 x 195 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, ii (contemporary paper) + 242 + ii (contemporary paper); [1-242]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by several hands.

origin.p: Written in Italy in the late 16th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
